column5: Hey fellows,  I'm planning to fish anstruther lake for the day on Saturday. Has anyone fished that lake? If so, hows the fishing and what species are there?  Thank you for your time guys!

i know from an excellent source, from a  cottage owner of many years on the lake, it's a good lake trout fishery. Was told that the lake is 230 feet at its deepest.  Never have fished the lake myself though...
lake trout small and large mouth bass perch at one point the mnr tried to stock walleye
Check the regs, i believe that is one of the lakes that is closed to winter fishing, and has been since 1986, along with Chandos and Eels etc
The original post was from back in August... FYI, if you are launching anything bigger than a canoe you might need a 4X4 to get in and out of the public ramp.
